%h1 Getting started
%h2 Step1: Add a node
%p
  You can add one or more nodes at #{link_to "New node", new_node_path}. Note that the word
  %b Node
  here means machine.

%h2 Step2: Create a proposal
%p
  After you have added nodes, you need to create a proposal to describe the software to be installed and the configuration of the software. The proposal can be created at #{link_to "New proposal", new_proposal_path}.
%p A default configuration has been prepared. You can use it without change, or customize it.

%h2 Step3: Install/uninstall/test a proposal
%p
  After you have created a proposal, you can install/uninstall/test the software described by the proposal at #{link_to "Proposals", proposals_path}. You can also confirm the operation at #{link_to "Logs", logs_path}.
%p
  You can find out what are the components which will be or has been installed in a node at #{link_to "Node configs", node_configs_path}.

%h2 Step4: edit/delete a proposal
%p
  You can modify a proposal or delete a proposal at #{link_to "Proposals", proposals_path}.

%h2 Step5: delete a node
%p
  If a node is no longer a target machine, you can delete it from #{link_to "Nodes", nodes_path}.
